OL,3,CHow much will your water provider
OL,4,Craise its bills by?
OL,6,FWater firms in England and Wales
OL,7,Fsubmit plans to Ofwat every five years
OL,8,Fon how much they will raise water
OL,9,Fbills.
OL,11,FOfwat then negotiates with the
OL,12,Fcompanies over how much bills can go
OL,13,Fup by and sets limits, before
OL,14,Fpublishing its final decision.
OL,16,FFor the next five years, Ofwat has
OL,17,Fgranted an average bills increase of
OL,18,F36%, or #31 a year until 2030. The
OL,19,Fregulator added this was, on average,
OL,20,F#8 lower per year compared to what
OL,21,Fcompanies proposed in their plans.
